</dl>
<figure id="attachment_115350"  class="wp-caption alignnone wp-caption-large cgrid-row" style="width: 700px"><div class="cgrid-col cgrid-col-span-full"><img class="size-ratio-large wp-image-115350" title="dark-template-700px" src="http://wpmu.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/dark-template-700px-700x698.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="698" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">A dark background, for you hackers out there ;)</figcaption></div></figure>
<p>And here&#8217;s one of my personalÂ favoriteÂ features, adding and managing users and groups:</p>
<figure id="attachment_115351"  class="wp-caption alignnone wp-caption-large cgrid-row" style="width: 700px"><div class="cgrid-col cgrid-col-span-full"><img class="size-ratio-large wp-image-115351" title="members-700px" src="http://wpmu.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/members-700px-700x429.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="429" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Easily add and manage and import individual and batches of email</figcaption></div></figure>
<dl id="attachment_115337" class="wp-caption alignnone cgrid-col-span-full" style="width: 559px;" data-variation="large" data-ratio="" data-position="">
<dt class="wp-caption-dt"><span style="color: #04243d; font-size: 16px;"><br />
And of course logged in users (for example, on Multisite or BuddyPress installations) can easily manage their email subscriptions via the widget, yum:<br />
</span></dt>
</dl>
<figure id="attachment_115352"  class="wp-caption alignnone wp-caption-large cgrid-row" style="width: 700px"><div class="cgrid-col cgrid-col-span-full"><img class="size-ratio-large wp-image-115352" title="widget-700px" src="http://wpmu.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/widget-700px-700x319.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="319" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Users can easily manage their subscriptions</figcaption></div></figure>
